  {
    "client_msg_id": "0a65ea31-1c19-4ef2-8ad1-aa6a2c9699d6",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "wasm internally to itself certainly doesn't support runtime codegen, as you have no access to the code at all (part of its security model), but you can generate a full wasm module, hand that back to the host (e.g. JS) to spin up a second wasm module. The future will give dynamic linking to make communication with such modules easier. Kind of like generating a DLL/.so at runtime, just easier",
    "user": "UHDQ62M4P",
    "ts": "1554174488.002200",
